{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Kupiansk |native_name = Куп'янськ |other_name = |image_skyline = Administration Building of Kupiansk Raion and Kupiansk City Council (10 2018) 01.jpg |imagesize = |image_caption = Kupiansk city council |image_flag = Kupjan h.png |image_shield = Kupyansk-herb.png |shield_size = 90px |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{UKR}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Oblast]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Raion]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Kharkiv Oblast]] |subdivision_name2 = |established_title = Founded |established_date = 1655 |leader_title = Mayor |leader_name = |area_total_km2 = 33.34 |population_total = 28 681 |population_as_of = 2017 |population_density_km2 = auto |postal_code_type = Postal code |postal_code = 63700-63709 |website = http://kupyansk.osp-ua.info/ |footnotes = |timezone = EET |utc_offset = +2 |timezone_DST = EEST |utc_offset_DST = +3 }} '''Kupiansk''' ({{lang-uk|Ку́п'янськ}}, [[Romanization of Ukrainian|translit.]] ''Kupyans’k'', {{lang-ru|Ку́пянск}}, {{lang|ru-latn|Kupyansk}}), is a [[city]] in [[Kharkiv Oblast]] ([[Oblast|province]]) of north-eastern [[Ukraine]]. Serving as the [[Capital (political)|administrative center]] of the [[Kupiansk Raion]] ([[Raion|district]]), the city itself is incorporated as a [[city of regional significance (Ukraine)|city of oblast significance]] and does not belong to the raion. It is an important railroad junction in the oblast. Population: {{Ua-pop-est2017|28,681}}
==Overview== [[File:ER9P-442-Kupyansk.jpg|thumb|left|Kupyansk railway station]] Kupiansk is located on the bank of the river [[Oskol River|Oskol]].
Kupiansk was occupied during [[World War II]] by the [[Wehrmacht|German Army]] from July 24, 1942 to February 3, 1943
Kupiansk is divided into three subparts, known as: Kupyansk (main part of town), [[Kupiansk-Vuzlovyi]] (where the train station is), and [[Kivsharivka]].
Kupyansk is about 2 1/2 hours from Kharkiv. There are connections by train or bus.
